chunk_content: For more examples and templates to support your DQA, please visit: 226 APPENDIX C: SITE AND SNU ATTRIBUTES AND EPIDEMIOLOGIC ESTIMATES Overview: PEPFAR collects administrative, epidemiologic, and service-related data about facilities and subnational units A P (SNUs) that help to better illuminate where services should be provided, where services are actually provided, who is P delivering these services, and what is the service capacity. Some of these attributes are routinely collected in the form of E MER indicators (e.g., HRH_STAFF_NAT), others are collected at the time a facility is added to a master facility list and N D subsequently DATIM (e.g., facility name, geographic coordinates), and others are collected during the annual PEPFAR I planning cycle. C E S Through the collection of these data, PEPFAR strives to have more complete information available on service provision and facility infrastructure.
